node.text:
Episode ✌️ of my 'How To' series is all about how to use the Cable & Pulley machine! 
This machine can look quite intimidating at first because there are so many parts to it. I've heard my clients say that they used to walk up to the machine and use whatever attachment is already there because they are too scared (or don't know how) to change them... which I totally understand.

Hopefully, this video will help you gain the confidence to firstly... use this machine, and secondly... use the machine exactly the way you want to! So next time you're in the gym, take me with you and give yourself the time to learn how these parts actually work. I promise it's easier than you have imagined! 😊

My High Intensity Strength program includes the use of this machine, and the @Sweat app will tell you exactly which attachment you need to complete the exercise which should help you build confidence, too! You can try my new gym program today via the link in my bio 😊

PS. All the videos that I will be sharing over the next week have been filmed before Adelaide's current lockdown. Stay safe ❤️

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Workout #Gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
INTRODUCING MY NEW 'HOW TO' SERIES - GYM EDITION 🌟
As gyms begin to re-open around the world, I want everyone to feel confident and comfortable getting back to their gym-based workouts.

I also know a lot of women feel intimidated about going to the gym, especially when it comes to using large equipment... so it's for these reasons I want to show you exactly HOW TO navigate a gym setting. In this series, I'll be taking you the step-by-step process as to how to set up and use different equipment around the gym.

To kick the series off, we're starting with the equipment that was requested most by YOU, #SWKCommunity...  THE LEG PRESS! 

We have a variety of gym-based programs in the @Sweat app that involves using the Leg Press, including my new and improved High-Intensity Strength program. So, next time you're in the gym... I want you to take me with you and allow yourself the time to get comfortable with using these bigger machines. Before you know it, you'll wish you stopped avoiding them sooner! 

I hope by the end of this episode you feel a lot LESS intimidated and a lot MORE empowered to use this machine in your training. 

If you're keen to start using the Leg Press in your workouts, I recommend trying my new and improved High Intensity Strength program. It uses larger machines, free weights and bodyweight exercises to help women get fitter and get stronger! You can try it today for free using @Sweat's 7-Day free trial (link in bio)!

It has been great to bring you even more new gym programs to Sweat and from now on we will be working with @iFIT to help deliver even more choice and variety to you all!

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #LegPress #gym #gymequipment #gymtutorial

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text: Let’s do this!! Take me anywhere with you and let’s train abs together !! (No equipment) EXPRESS WORKOUT

"But Kayla, I don't have time to workout today!!" 
... are you sure about that?! 🤣🤣

If this sounds like you, I'm here to tell you that there is almost ALWAYS time to squeeze in a workout! You just have to start telling yourself that any amount of time working out it's worth it! 
 
I've created this 5-minute "follow-along" lower body workout that should have you breaking a sweat and feeling accomplished in a short amount of time! I'm ready to work out with you right now, but it's up to YOU to set aside the time to get your body moving today! 

✅ Squat Pulse - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Curtsey Lunge - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

✅ Glute Bridge Walkout - 20 secs
- Rest for 10 secs

 Do 3 laps

✅ Squat Pulse finisher - 30 secs

I certainly felt the burn after that!! Did you? 🔥😅

If you love the thought of an express workout - there are SO many incredible programs in the @Sweat app that are ready and waiting for you! Head to the link in my bio for a 7-Day free trial and get moving today!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla 

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatwithKayla #SweatCommunity #ExpressWorkout #Workout

Are your glute bridges actually working your glutes? Or just hurting your lower back? 🤔
Glute bridges are one of those exercises that look quite easy to do... but they can hurt the wrong muscles if done incorrectly! 

I've noticed that some people push their hips as high as they can, causing them to over-extend and put pressure on their lower back. If this sounds like you, or you haven't been feeling the burn in your glutes when doing glute bridges, I want you to watch this video and practice my number one tip! 

You should absolutely be feeling your glutes burn if you do this! 🔥
Let me know if this has helped you!

node.text:
This is an easy one to get wrong ❌ 
So if you do Ab Bikes often, I want you to take the time to learn how to get them right! ✅

In this video, I break down the exercise into smaller steps to help you perfect your form. Once you've mastered each movement, add each step in until you build up to a full Ab Bike! 

Here are some do's and don'ts to remember:
DO
✅Rest hands in front of ears
✅Rotate at the torso
✅Bring knees in close to the chest
✅Extend your legs in a push and pull motion
✅Elevate your shoulders

DON'T
❌Pull your neck up with your hands behind your head
❌Do small in and out motions with your legs
❌Curve your back away from the floor

What other exercises do you want to learn from me? Comment below!

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatwithKayla

node.text:
Right, so today I'm going to break down the burpee for you to make it easier.

It's still not going to be EASY (it's a burpee haha!!)... but these tips will make it easier to do 😅⁣ You're still going to #SweatwithKayla and you'll find burpees in my High Intensity program. There's a link in my bio for a 7 day FREE trial of the @Sweat app. 

Follow this and see how it feels:
✅Start at the top of your mat
✅Put your hands down in front of your feet as you squat down
✅Jump back into a push up position
✅Make sure your wrist and shoulder is in line
✅Back nice and straight
✅Make sure you're stable and have a strong core 
✅Jump back in with feet apart (not together!)
✅Stand up and do your jump
✅Find your rhythm

Some common mistakes:
❌Starting with your hands too far in front of you 
❌Not holding your core tight throughout each movement
❌Letting your back dip down into an unstable position
❌Jumping in too far with your feet and putting pressure on your knees
❌Arching your back too much before jumping to a standing position

Now, I've shown you the correct technique how do your burpees feel?

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

For a lot of women around the world, the last 12 months have been tough. For many of you it meant an adjustment to working out at home, or perhaps, it meant losing the time, space or motivation to work out all together. I want you to know that you’re not alone in facing these challenges. We see you and and at @Sweat we want to help.

I want to introduce you to Sweat’s new MOVE AGAIN programs, designed specifically for those who have had a break in their fitness journey due to the pandemic.

These four new beginner level programs consist of two 20-minute workouts a week for four weeks and are led by four inspiring trainers that are dedicated to help you form healthy habits and get you back into fitness. 

👉 Bodyweight Strength with Anissia (@avh__fitness)
🌟 When Anissia isn’t playing basketball, she’s all about strength and bodyweight circuits. Her approach to fitness is all about getting back to basics and her Bodyweight Strength workouts require absolutely no equipment.

👉 Low Impact HIIT with Samantha (@so_manti)
🌟 With Samantha you can expect a fast-paced and upbeat style to her Low Impact HIIT workouts which are perfect for getting a quick sweat up in a short amount of time.

👉 Strength & Cardio with Marilyn (@fitwithmarilyn)
🌟 Marilyn’s approach to fitness is about maximising your time with fun and dynamic workouts to help you build form and to find your love for moving again. You’ll feel strong off the back of these workouts and the combination of rep based strength and timed based cardio.

👉 Low Impact Strength with Kelsey (@kelseywells)
🌟 Now Kelsey is one of my best friends and she has been part of the Sweat family for a while now and we so are excited to be adding a low-impact strength program. Kelsey’s new dumbbell based workouts are great to build your confidence using weights and will have you feeling strong again in no time.

We’ve designed each program to support your physical and mental health. We want you to remember how good it feels to move again!

So why not take advantage of our Sweat 7-day free trial and start moving again

www.kaylaitsines.com/moveagain

#MoveAgain #Sweat #Sweatcommunity #SWKcommunity #KaylaItsines

I absolutely LOVE doing ab workouts, and clearly many of you ladies in the #SweatCommunity feel the same way because they are my most requested workouts! ⁣😍
⁣
This Advanced Ab Follow Along uses ZERO equipment and will put most people through their paces. 5 minutes of 5 exercises with a rest in-between each, let's do this! 

✅ Single-Arm and Leg Jackknife - 45 sec
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Straight-Leg Raise & Hip Lift - 45 sec
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Bent Leg Toe Taps - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ X Plank - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec
✅ Plank - 45 sec 
✅ Rest - 15 sec

Complete 1 lap!

This is perfect to add on to the end of your workouts, so I want you to SAVE this video next time you train! For even more ab workouts like this try my Zero Equipment program @Sweat today! 

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #AbsWorkout #ZeroEquipment #Sweat

node.text:
I wanted to give you an overview about my programs on @sweat so you can decide which one is right for you!
Their names may have changed but why I designed them and what you can get out of them HASN'T. 

I believe I have a program for EVERYONE, you just need to find one that suits YOU! 👇

👉 HIGH INTENSITY WITH KAYLA (formerly BBG)
✅ High intensity 28 minute workouts. This is my original and most well known program, completed by thousands of women like you all around the world! It has been designed to help women achieve their fitness goals with short and very effective workouts. This is THE program to become fitter, stronger and more confident!
 
👉 HIGH INTENSITY ZERO EQUIPMENT WITH KAYLA (formerly BBG Zero Equipment) 
✅ All workouts in this program are similar to my High Intensity program, but they require ZERO equipment so you can do them anytime, anywhere! The workouts are all less than 28 minutes. All you need is YOU!!.... and some water haha.

👉 HIGH INTENSITY STRENGTH⁣ WITH KAYLA (formerly BBG Stronger)
✅ I designed this program to help women to feel confident and comfortable in the gym and around big gym equipment. My program allows you to get the most out of your time at the gym with easy to follow structured workouts that build from beginner through to advanced. 
⁣
👉 LOW IMPACT WITH KAYLA
✅ #LowImpactwithKayla This is my NO JUMPING PROGRAM and is for all women no matter what your age or fitness level. It's perfect if you're just starting out, or are returning to fitness after injury or a break. The workouts are low intensity and can all be done in under 30 minutes

✅ #PostPregnancy I created this program to support women who are looking to regain their strength and fitness after pregnancy and birth. The workouts include low-impact exercises and short - ranging from 15 to 25 minutes. Please ensure you have clearance from your healthcare professional

If you're just starting out, if you’re new to @sweat, or if you’re looking for a new challenge, you can train with me! Download Sweat now and take advantage of our 7-day free trial and give my programs a go. 💪⁣

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #Sweatcommunity

node.text:
It has been almost 10 years since I created BBG with the positive intent that every BODY is a bikini body. However, I feel the name now represents an outdated view of health and fitness so as co-founder of Sweat, I feel it is the right time to change our approach with BBG and to evolve and use language that feels more positive for women today.

So I've made the decision to rename my programs from BBG and replace it with ‘High Intensity’. As you can imagine this is a huge moment for me personally as my programs with the BBG name are so well known and have been a massive part of building one of THE biggest female fitness communities in the world.

Since having Arna, I’ve become even more aware of how important it is that we use language that EMPOWERS women. I want to use language that is completely positive and inspiring for all women and that is the world I want Arna to grow up in. Over the last 10 years I've learnt that how we communicate to women and the language we use really MATTERS. 

I feel SO positive about this change. I'm proud that as a company at @sweat we can look at something and think that 'that's not good enough' or 'that's not right anymore' and make the relevant changes.  

All of my BBG program names will change in the Sweat app and you'll start to see their names changing in other places too, like my website and my social channels over the next few weeks.

I want to reassure anyone doing my programs that absolutely NOTHING will change with the programs themselves. So if you are doing BBG now you will see your program is now called High Intensity with Kayla on the Sweat app but the program will be the same. 

So here are all of your new program names (remember the programs themselves are are not changing):

High Intensity with Kayla (formerly BBG)
High Intensity Strength with Kayla (formerly BBG Stronger) 
High Intensity Zero Equipment with Kayla (formerly BBG Zero Equipment)
Low Impact with Kayla (program name remains the same)
Post-Pregnancy with Kayla (program name remains the same)

You can see these name changes on the @sweat app now. 

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SweatwithKayla #SWKcommunity #Sweatcommunity
#BBG #BBGCommunity

I've been in the fitness industry for more than 10 YEARS and honestly, I'm embarrassed to say that my mum has never actually wanted to train with me before .....until now. 

I created my new Low Impact program for my mum, and all women like her, who have never been interested in doing my programs before because they have been too high intensity and had too much jumping in them. Low Impact has NO JUMPING at all!

Watch what she had to say when we sat down to talk about us training together and how she has found my new Low Impact program. 

If you want to give my new Low Impact program a go, then head to the link in my bio to start your FREE 7-day @Sweat trial today. It's been made especially for women who may be just starting out or returning to fitness after a break, it is gentle on your joints and there's absolutely NO jumping! 

www.kaylaitsines.com/LowImpactWithKayla

node.text:
Episode ✌️ of my 'How To' series is all about how to use the Cable & Pulley machine! 
This machine can look quite intimidating at first because there are so many parts to it. I've heard my clients say that they used to walk up to the machine and use whatever attachment is already there because they are too scared (or don't know how) to change them... which I totally understand.

Hopefully, this video will help you gain the confidence to firstly... use this machine, and secondly... use the machine exactly the way you want to! So next time you're in the gym, take me with you and give yourself the time to learn how these parts actually work. I promise it's easier than you have imagined! 😊

My High Intensity Strength program includes the use of this machine, and the @Sweat app will tell you exactly which attachment you need to complete the exercise which should help you build confidence, too! You can try my new gym program today via the link in my bio 😊

PS. All the videos that I will be sharing over the next week have been filmed before Adelaide's current lockdown. Stay safe ❤️

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #SweatApp #Workout #Gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
5 REASONS TO STAY HYDRATED... 💧👇
It's easy to forget just how important water is for our body! I find that if I'm well hydrated, not only are my energy levels higher in general, but I get tend to get the most out of my workouts AND my recovery when I've had a good amount of water.

Most of us know (or have experienced first-hand) the negative effects of dehydration... So, I wanted to point out the benefits of drinking water, which will hopefully motivate you to focus on hydration today & every day! 

So, here are the reasons why I always try to stay hydrated! 👇

💧My mood is generally so much better when I am well hydrated! There's no time for a nasty headache to get in the way of a good day! 

💧My energy levels are a lot higher when I have had a good amount of water... which is very important for my High Intensity workouts (or any type of workout for that matter!) 

💧I can concentrate properly when I'm hydrated and can stay focused on tasks for longer.

💧My skin complexion always shows when I've been drinking water! Hydrated body = hydrated skin (which is always a plus!).

💧My body seems to recover a lot faster when I've kept my hydration levels up and I tend to avoid things like muscle cramps and body aches! 

So remember - being properly hydrated will help your body to function at its absolute best. By simply increasing your daily water intake you can start to notice huge improvements in how you feel. 

#SWKCommunity - tag someone that needs a reminder to drink water today! 

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Sweat #SweatApp #Motivation

node.text:
#SWKCommunity, I want to hear about your WHY! ❤️

It’s so important to have a ‘why’ on your journey! Your why gives you a sense of purpose, and a reason for what you are doing. That doesn’t mean it has to be a big, extreme purpose or goal, as that can feel daunting to achieve. It can be a small reason, or a big specific goal - it’s YOUR ‘why’ to choose! 

Do you complete your workouts just to get that big rush of endorphins? Or maybe you have a particular fitness goal that you are working towards! Having something that keeps you going when things get tough is like the light at the end of the tunnel - you know that good things are going to come! 

Why do you stay on track to your goals? I would love for you to comment below and share your ‘why’ with the community! 👇

We’ve got this 👊

Look at Michelle’s (@michworksout) incredible effort!! Not only are you smashing your goals, but I love hearing about your journey too. Everyone starts as a beginner, and while it’s not always easy, I’m so proud of the confidence and discipline that you have gained along the way! 😍😍

Michelle says: “Two years ago, I started using @kayla_itsines BBG program (now High Intensity with Kayla) and got really serious about my fitness journey. This is after losing a lot of weight with just diet and some exercising, but I was ready to commit to a program and get serious with my journey. I am so glad I did because this helped me stay committed to a routine and motivated while seeing the changes in my body.

Being a beginner is so hard, especially after losing all my ab muscles from having my son, but you have to start somewhere. I kept making excuses until I finally stopped and did something to better myself instead.”

The best way to start is by starting, and look where you are now Michelle! 🤩🤩 If you want to get started with your first workout from my program, head to the link in my bio to download the @Sweat app today!

www.KaylaItsines.com/SweatWithKayla

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SweatCommunity #Progress #Fitness #SWKCommunity

node.text:
Top tip - create a list of 'MUST HAVES' that you NEED to do every single day to keep you happy. Then, work everything else around these things. That is my key to a happy, balanced lifestyle. Here's mine.👇

1. Arna! ❤️ Being a mum to Arna is always my number 1 priority. I work my day around her routine and that will never change. 

2. Exercise! 💦 Moving my body is a must every day, but I only workout or walk for around 28 minutes a day! 

3. Help someone! 🙆 Whether it's for friends, family or a stranger... I try to do at least one thing that helps someone every day.

4. Family! 👪 I HAVE to see at least one member of my family every day... this is absolutely a non-negotiable! My sister, parents, grandparents and I ALWAYS make time for eachother! 

5. Food! 🍲 I always look forward to eating, so I make sure I enjoy every meal of the day! This includes family dinners at mum and dad's or my Grandparent's house at least 4 times a week (pls refer to point #4 🤣). I love sharing food with good company so this is an important one! 

6. SWEAT! 👩‍💻 Now this is one aspect of my life that is so fulfilling, but also, very time-consuming! I know many of you see my face in the Sweat app every single day, and there's  A LOT of work that is done behind the scenes to bring these programs to life! As many of you know, I am co-founder of Sweat ... which means A LOT of meetings, A LOT of problem solving and A LOT of time in front of the computer. I love being so involved in every part of the business, so I make sure the parts of my life I mentioned above are all in check so that I can show up and support my amazing team at @Sweat and this incredible community every day.

#SWKCommunity - what are your must-haves every single day?

#SWK #SweatWithKayla #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #motivation

MY FAVOURITE EXERCISES FROM MY HIGH INTENSITY STRENGTH PROGRAM
.... Okay, this was hard!! 😅 I LOVE working out in a gym, and this new program combines big machines, with free weight and bodyweight exercises which are 3 of my FAVOURITE things to do in a workout! 

So, I have narrowed my favourite High Intesnity Strength exercises down to 5 for now... but honestly, they are likely to change again tomorrow 🤣 👇
1️⃣ Lat Pulldown 
2️⃣ Hip-Thrust
3️⃣ Weighted Step-Up
4️⃣ Lateral Lunge
5️⃣ Burpee Box Jump (this was a given 😜)

If you love these exercises too, or want to start doing them in your training, I recommend trying out my new High Intensity Strength Program in the @Sweat app via the link in my bio! 

PS. I just wanted to say that there once was a time that I was intimidated by some of the gym equipment in this video, too. Looking back, I NEVER thought that exercises using big machines like these would become some of my favorites. I just thought it was important to say that, because I know there are a lot of women out there that would never imagine themselves working out like this. Everyone has a day one... including me. Just remember that. ❤️

#SWKCommunity #SWK #SweatCommunity #Exercise #Workout #Gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

node.text:
Swipe to see my face when someone says using weights in a gym makes you bulky..... 🙄 👉

There is a misconception out there that using weights will make you “turn into a bodybuilder”.... which is SO far from true. That’s like saying you will “turn into” a surgeon if you put a bandaid on someone’s finger. It takes SO much time, effort, training and resilience to do bodybuilding. It’s basically a full-time job! 

In my new gym program, using weights for around 30 minutes 3-4 times per week combined with cardio will absolutely NOT make you 'bulky' - AT ALL 💪❤️ I have been training with weights for YEARS and 'bulky' is not how I would describe my body....

My new and improved High Intensity Strength program has been designed specifically for the gym, in a format that allows you to spend more time in one area of the gym, with either free weights, equipment, or no equipment at all! I'm SO excited that you can finally try it! Link in bio to download the @Sweat app today! 

#SWK #SWKcommunity #SweatCommunity #workout #gym #gymworkout 

www.kaylaitsines.com/HighIntensityStrengthWithKayla

Comfort zones are exactly that: comfortable! It can be hard to push yourself to try something new. But that's where the growth happens. If you're dreaming of something bigger, you HAVE to do something new. 

So #SWKCommunity, that's your Challenge for this week. I want you to do ONE thing this week that you've never done before.

It could be saying hi to a stranger at the gym, or actually using that piece of equipment you've always avoided. Maybe it's trying a new recipe or signing up for a brand new fitness class... 

Whatever it is, be honest with yourself and challenge yourself - you don't know what you are capable of until you change things up! 

I cannot wait to see that the future brings now Sweat is part of the @iFIT family. We are going to empower women more than ever before.

#SWK #SWKCommunity #SweatCommunity #Motivation #Quote 

www.kaylaitsines.com/SweatWithKayla

node.text:
Putting the spotlight on @kar.sweats.bbg 🤩🤩 I just LOVE Karina’s positivity and attitude about her fitness journey! It’s so important to celebrate all of your wins along the way - it’s not about the destination, but how you get there! 💪You are not only looking so strong and happy, but your confidence is shining through!! 😍

@kar.sweats.bbg says “Life is a journey not a destination, and that is so so right! Keep going babes because this journey it's not ending, we have to enjoy the process because this is our life and we only have one!

Good changes don't happen overnight, it takes effort and determination to achieve them, and I am talking about any aspect of life, the commitment must be yours and no one else's . . . 

. . . The effort is worth it! I love taking before and after photos because I can see how far I have come and it is a good point of reference, but what is not seen in the pic is what I have acquired mentally, the attitude and perseverance to want to be a healthy person.

I'm not perfect and I definitely don't want to be, I love what I see every day in the mirror.

Thank you @kayla_itsines for guiding me on this journey.”

Karina, I am so proud of your hard work! Keep it up for the rest of the #SweatChallenge and beyond 😍

I can’t wait to see what the future holds and how many more women we can empower now that we have @iFIT’s help.

Head to the link in my bio for a 7-Day free trial to get started on your fitness journey with @Sweat too! 

#SWK #SweatwithKayla #SweatCommunity #Progress #Fitness #Transformation
